  <h1>From 13 Life Cycle Hooks to 2!</h1>
  <p>Glimmer Components have just two lifecycle hooks - the <strong>constructor</strong> function for setting up the component, and the <strong>willDestroy</strong> function for tearing it down. It also has just 3 properties: isDestroying, isDestroyed, and args.
</p><p>
Turns out most of the life cycle hooks had a lot of overlap and we an achieve the same stuff with getters and modifiers. Below example uses 
Ember Render Modifiers <strong>ember install @ember/render-modifiers</strong></p>
  <div class="hbs">
    {{#let (get-code-snippet "modifier.hbs") as |snippet|}}
